problem.markdown:
Try to guess the demographics of the OMSCS program! (OMSCS demographics are based on the 400 students in CS7637: Knowledge-Based AI in Summer 2015)

>>What percentage of OMSCS students lived in the United States immediately before they began their Master's Degree?<<
( ) 13% {{ Way too low! In fact, that's the percentage of OMSCS students that do *not* live in the United States. }}
( ) 32% {{ You're right!... about the on-campus program. Only 32% of on-campus students lived in the United States before they started their Master's Degree. }}
( ) 68% {{ Not quite! 68% of on-campus students did not live in the United States before beginning their Master's Degree. }}
(x) 87% {{ That's right! The online program is largely domestic, which surprised us at first. }}

[explanation]
87% of OMSCS students lived in the United States before beginning their Master's Degree. While the program draws a big international audience in terms of raw numbers (approximately 500 international students), the domestic students dominate in terms of percentages.
[explanation]
